          <span class="dlm-tag" style="color:rgba(232,192,110,0.7);border-color:rgba(232,192,110,0.12);">Gaucher</span>
          <span class="dlm-tag" style="color:rgba(232,192,110,0.7);border-color:rgba(232,192,110,0.12);">Wolman</span>
          <span class="dlm-tag" style="color:rgba(232,192,110,0.5);border-color:rgba(232,192,110,0.08);">+10 more</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ═══ CORD TISSUE SCROLLYTELLING ═══ -->
<section class="scrolly scrolly-tissue" id="scrollyCT">
  <div class="stitle stitle-sticky section-enter">
    <div class="sr" data-d="0">
      <div class="stitle-pill" style="border-color:rgba(42,107,79,0.2);">
        <span style="color:#5DB890;">Cord Tissue</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="sr" data-d="150">
      <h2>What are cord tissue stem cells?</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="sr" data-d="400">
      <p class="stitle-sub" style="font-size:15px;color:var(--muted);max-width:460px;margin:12px auto 0;line-height:1.7;">Your umbilical cord contains a second type of stem cell — one that doesn't build blood, but repairs and rebuilds the body itself.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="scrolly-inner">
    <div class="scrolly-text">
      <div class="scrolly-step" data-tstep="0"><div class="scrolly-step-inner active">
        <div class="step-num" style="color:rgba(42,107,79,0.3)">05</div>
        <h2 style="color:var(--sage)">There's more than blood in the cord</h2>
        <p>The umbilical cord itself — the tissue — contains a different type of stem cell called <strong>mesenchymal stem cells (MSCs)</strong>. They live inside a jelly-like substance called Wharton's jelly.</p>
      </div></div>
      <div class="scrolly-step" data-tstep="1"><div class="scrolly-step-inner">
        <div class="step-num" style="color:rgba(42,107,79,0.3)">06</div>
        <h2 style="color:var(--sage)">They repair, not replace</h2>
        <p>Where cord blood rebuilds your blood and immune system, cord tissue MSCs repair <strong>structural tissue — muscle, bone, cartilage, skin, and organs</strong>. They're the body's construction crew.</p>
      </div></div>
      <div class="scrolly-step" data-tstep="2"><div class="scrolly-step-inner">
        <div class="step-num" style="color:rgba(42,107,79,0.3)">07</div>
        <h2 style="color:var(--sage)">That changes everything</h2>
        <p>A cell that can repair tissue means potential treatments for <strong>Alzheimer's, Parkinson's, spinal cord injuries, diabetes, arthritis</strong> — conditions that affect millions and currently have no cure. Over 500 clinical trials are underway worldwide.</p>
      </div></div>
      <div class="scrolly-step" data-tstep="3"><div class="scrolly-step-inner">
        <div class="step-num" style="color:rgba(42,107,79,0.3)">08</div>
        <h2 style="color:var(--sage)">No matching required</h2>
        <p>Unlike cord blood, MSCs <strong>don't require HLA matching</strong>. That means they could potentially be used by any family member — parents, siblings, even grandparents — without the compatibility barrier.</p>
      </div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="scrolly-visual"><canvas id="arcCanvas"></canvas></div>
  </div>
  <div class="scrolly-spacer" style="height:50vh;"></div>
</section>

<!-- ═══ MANIFESTO: Cord Tissue Future ═══ -->
<section class="manifesto-section section-enter" id="manifesto">
  <canvas id="manifestoCanvas"></canvas>
  <div class="manifesto-content">
    <div style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:72px;">
      <div class="sr" data-d="0" style="font-size:11px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:2px;text-transform:uppercase;color:#5DB890;margin-bottom:12px;">Cord Tissue Research</div>
      <div class="sr" data-d="150" style="font-family:'Playfair Display',serif;font-size:44px;font-weight:400;line-height:1.2;color:#fff;">Ten reasons cord tissue<br>is the future of medicine.</div>
      <div class="sr" data-d="300" style="font-size:15px;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.3);max-width:440px;margin:12px auto 0;">One collection. One moment. A lifetime of possibilities that science is just beginning to unlock.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="manifesto-list" id="manifestoList">
      <div class="manifesto-line"></div>
    </div>
    <div style="text-align:center;margin-top:56px;" id="statArea">
      <div id="stat500" style="font-family:'Source Serif 4',serif;font-size:56px;color:rgba(93,184,144,0.12);transition:all 0.8s cubic-bezier(0.16,1,0.3,1);">500+</div>
      <div id="stat500label" style="font-size:13px;font-weight:600;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.25);margin-top:-4px;transition:all 0.8s cubic-bezier(0.16,1,0.3,1);letter-spacing:0.5px;">active MSC clinical trials worldwide</div>
    </div>
    <div style="text-align:center;margin-top:28px;">
      <a href="/clinical-trials" class="manifesto-cta">View StemCyte clinical trials <span style="font-size:16px;">&#8594;</span></a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- CTA BANNER -->
<section class="cta-banner anim">
  <h2>What happens if you don't <em>bank?</em></h2>
  <p>If your baby's cord blood is not collected at birth, it's discarded as medical waste. There is no way to go back.</p>
  <div class="btns">
    <a href="/pricing" class="btn-w">View plans &amp; pricing</a>
    <a href="tel:8663894659" class="btn-gd">Call (866) 389-4659</a>
  </div>
